Lagos – Super Eagles midfielder, Wilfred Ndidi, is on the verge of dumping Leicester City for Liverpool FC all things being equal. Liverpool reportedly have agreed terms with FIFA World Cup bound player as the club is set to lose Emre Can.
The German international, Can is likely to leave Anfield as his contract expires in the summer.
He is yet to agree terms with the club amid links with Italian champions Juventus.
RB Leipzig’s Naby Keita was signed last year on the condition he spent one last season in the Bundesliga.
Leicester ace Ndidi has been earmarked as a target by Liverpool in the past as they search for an energetic defensive midfielder.
And Balde has revealed that the club has agreed terms with the Nigeria international.
“Ndidi approached by Liverpool. The player has agreed. It remains to agree with Leicester, who asks a lot,” Balde tweeted.
The 21-year-old has enjoyed his time at the King Power Stadium since joining in January 2017.
